<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 5:44PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Talladega, southwestern Cleburne and northeastern Clay Counties
through 615 PM CDT...
At 544 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mount Cheaha, or near Oxford. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Oxford, Munford, Anniston Regional Airport, Grant Town, Mount Cheaha,
Camp Mac, Jenifer and Lake Chinnabee.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
